&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT PHYSICIAN ACUTE MEDICINE – full time &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Royal is pleased to advertise a consultant post in Acute Medicine as part of our expansion of the service. This is to enable us to provide first class care to our patients with early input from a senior doctor, rapid signposting to the best clinical area and to further develop services such as ED in reach, triage, Same Day Emergency Care (SDEC) and 7 day services to complement our established Consultant led seven day Short Stay Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chesterfield Royal is a forward thinking Foundation Trust, always striving to improve services through transformation. It is set in a great location, being an attractive market town close to the major cities of Nottingham and Sheffield and only 10 minutes travelling time from the Peak District National Park, which is an area of outstanding natural beauty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the job description for further details about our hospital and department. Interested candidates and those who wish to offer a subspecialty interest are strongly encouraged to get in touch to discuss how you could be part of our future plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants for the post should ideally hold a CCT in Acute Medicine but those with General Internal Medicine and appropriate acute medical experience are also welcome to apply (or be within six months of receiving a CCT at the date of interview). Requests for flexible working arrangements and special interests will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
